2026-04-13 15:26:47,238 INFO RLM iteration 2/50
Reasoning: We have inspected the workbook: it contains a header row and product codes in column A, with manual unique IDs in column B. The task is to generate a unique sequential number for each distinct product automatically, using a formula in column B. We'll overwrite column B (starting at row 2) with a formula that assigns a new ID the the product appears for the first time, otherwise looks up the previously assigned ID. The formula will be: =IF(COUNTIF($A$2:A{row}, A{row})=1, IFERROR(MAX($B$1:B{row-1}),0)+1, VLOOKUP(A{row}, $A$2:B{row-1}, 2, FALSE)). We'll write this formula into each cell in column B, save the workbook to the output directory, then reload it with data_only=True to verify a few generated IDs.
Code:
```repl
import openpyxl
from pathlib import Path

# Paths
input_path = Path(input_spreadsheet)
output_dir = Path("/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet")
output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
output_path = output_dir / input_path.name

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]

max_row = ws.max_row

# Write formula into column B for rows 2..max_row
for r in range(2, max_row + 1):
    # Build formula with current row number
    formula = (
        f"=IF(COUNTIF($A$2:A{r}, A{r})=1, "
        f"IFERROR(MAX($B$1:B{r-1}),0)+1, "
        f"VLOOKUP(A{r}, $A$2:B{r-1}, 2, FALSE))"
    )
    ws.cell(row=r, column=2).value = formula

# Save workbook
wb.save(output_path)

# Verify by loading with data_only to see computed values (LibreOffice recalculation not run here, but we can at least check formulas are written)
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
print(f"Saved to {output_path}")
print("Sample rows after writing formulas (A, B):")
for r in range(1, min(6, ws_check.max_row+1)):
    a = ws_check.cell(row=r, column=1).value
    b = ws_check.cell(row=r, column=2).value
    print(f"Row {r}: A={a!r}, B={b!r}")
```
